                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15313195" author="apachespark" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 22:20:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;mengxr&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13478&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13478&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313198" author="mengxr" created="Thu, 2 Jun 2016 22:24:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tmnd91&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tmnd91&quot;&gt;tmnd91&lt;/a&gt; Could you run the test and estimate how much ram does it need? Btw, we should set spark.kryoserializer.buffer.max to a small value instead of creating a big array for the test. Do you have time to look into this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313754" author="tmnd91" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2016 06:50:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking into it right now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15313830" author="tmnd91" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2016 08:15:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In order to set a small partition size w/r/t spark.kryoserializer.buffer.max I need to read that conf in the first place and change the word2vecserializer code to be adaptive. I think i can retrieve the conf with:&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
spark.conf.get(&quot;spark.kryoserializer.buffer.max&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;br/&gt;
But then how could i convert the string in a format like &quot;64m&quot; to the number of bytes? Is there a utile somewhere to take advantage of?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I purpose to make the partitioning adaptive to that value and to set a small spark.kryoserializer.buffer.max to a small size only for the test, therefore we&apos;ll need a small array avoiding OOMs.&lt;br/&gt;
Let me know what do you think about it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15314816" author="mengxr" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2016 21:08:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The proposal looks good to me. Please also try to measure the memory requirement so we can easily tell whether the issue is fixed or not. Triggering Jenkins maven builds is not convenient.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15315394" author="tmnd91" created="Sat, 4 Jun 2016 08:39:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As of now the memory requirement would be something like 2k.&lt;br/&gt;
I made a pull request named &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15740&quot; title=&quot;Word2VecSuite &amp;quot;big model load / save&amp;quot; caused OOM in maven jenkins builds&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-15740&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-15740&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I was able to run it successfully, but I don&apos;t know how to measure the memory req. of the test. Can you point me to some resource where I can learn how to?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15315399" author="apachespark" created="Sat, 4 Jun 2016 08:43:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;tmnd1991&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13509&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/13509&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
